ur first week with our product. What was the first thing you tried to do after signing up?\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"message\": \"Sounds great. So yeah, the first thing I wanted to do after I sign up is essentially just understanding the product. So, uh, that's, like, one of the most important things when I understand, like, a product from the beginning, and I think like, \\\"Okay, that's cool. I want to, I want to have that product,\\\" and then I sign up, and essentially, I just want to figure out immediately how it works, the features, and stuff like that.\"}, {\"role\": \"agent\", \"message\": \"That makes sense, wanting to get a clear overview right away is very common. Was there a moment in your first few days where you felt stuck or unsure what to do next?\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"message\": \"No, no, not at all.\"}, {\"role\": \"agent\", \"message\": \"That is great to hear that you felt confident navigating the product early on. What almost made you stop using the product, if anything?\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"message\": \"Um, actually, I think one thing that is kind of annoying is that essentially the product has so many features that you often feel kind of overwhelmed by what it can do or what it can't do. So I think that's something which is to be considered because essentially you can just have the ability to concentrate on the quality of the product and not per se just, like, looping through multiple different functionalities.\"}, {\"role\": \"agent\", \"message\": \"Thank you for that honest feedback about feeling overwhelmed by the number of features. If you could change one thing about the first-time experience, what would it be?\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"message\": \"Maybe because right now you don't have, like, a run-through agent what helps the person to onboard. Something like that could really help, uh, new users to understand your product.\"}, {\"role\": \"agent\", \"message\": \"That is a valuable suggestion about adding a guided agent 